<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-27T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-27T06:00:00-05:00" n="727" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">840.48 Refugees/409: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Luxemburg</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Waller</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Luxemburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-27T12:00:00+01:00">June 27,
                            1938—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received June 27—9 a.m.]</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>16. I have strongest reason to believe that the Grand Ducal Government,
                        having a refugee problem of its own and lying on German frontier, desirous
                        of cooperating in refugee questions, would welcome an invitation to be
                        represented at meeting at Evian on July 6. Please instruct.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Waller</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>